Singing sensation Brymo has taken a swipe at Nigerians living abroad. The controversial singer took to his Twitter account to disparage the Nigerians who left for abroad seeking greener pastures yet heap blames on the country. “Folks move abroad and talk shit like ‘if only Nigeria worked, we’ll all move back home’ Nigeria na person wey go fix their-self… una go come return to chop.. lol’   21 shops razed in Kamba as Bagudu directs immediate repair     APC National Convention will hold in February — Governors     Buhari renews crackdown on bandits’ order to military   Brymo has been in the news for several reasons and has continued to court controversies with his tweets and opinions on social, economic and political issues. - Advertisement - Brymo made it big while signed to Chocolate City records under Audu Maikori and some of his biggest songs include Ara and Oleku featuring Iceprince and others.